<div class="container my-5">
  <h1 class="mb-4">üí∞ DMN Real-World Pricing Example</h1>

  <div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>About Real-World Pricing:</strong> This example demonstrates complex e-commerce pricing logic using DMN.
    It handles customer segments, product categories, volume discounts, and promotional codes with PRIORITY hit policy.
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
          <h5 class="mb-0">Calculate Pricing</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <%= form_with url: demo_dmn_real_world_pricing_path, method: :post, local: true do |f| %>
            <div class="mb-3">
              <%= f.label :customer_segment, "Customer Segment", class: "form-label" %>
              <%= f.select :customer_segment, [['VIP', 'vip'], ['Premium', 'premium'], ['Standard', 'standard']], { selected: 'standard' }, { class: "form-control" } %>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
              <%= f.label :product_category, "Product Category", class: "form-label" %>
              <%= f.select :product_category, [['Electronics', 'electronics'], ['Books', 'books'], ['Clothing', 'clothing']], { selected: 'electronics' }, { class: "form-control" } %>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
              <%= f.label :quantity, "Quantity", class: "form-label" %>
              <%= f.number_field :quantity, value: 1, min: 1, class: "form-control" %>
              <small class="form-text text-muted">Bulk discounts apply for 10+ units</small>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
              <%= f.label :promo_code, "Promotional Code", class: "form-label" %>
              <%= f.text_field :promo_code, value: '', class: "form-control", placeholder: "e.g., SUMMER2024" %>
            </div>

            <%= f.submit "Calculate Discount", class: "btn btn-primary" %>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
      <% if @result %>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
            <h5 class="mb-0">Pricing Result</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <% if @result[:error] %>
              <div class="alert alert-danger">
                <strong>Error:</strong> <%= @result[:error] %>
              </div>
            <% else %>
              <div class="mb-3">
                <strong>Discount Percentage:</strong>
                <span class="badge bg-success" style="font-size: 1.2em;">
                  <%= @result[:discount_percentage] %>%
                </span>
              </div>

              <div class="mb-3">
                <strong>Pricing Tier:</strong>
                <span class="badge bg-info"><%= @result[:tier] || 'standard' %></span>
              </div>

              <div class="mb-3">
                <strong>Decision Value:</strong> <%= @result[:decision] %>
              </div>

              <div class="mb-3">
                <strong>Confidence:</strong> <%= (@result[:confidence] * 100).round(1) %>%
              </div>

              <div class="mb-3">
                <strong>Reason:</strong>
                <p class="text-muted"><%= @result[:reason] %></p>
              </div>

              <% if @result[:metadata] %>
                <details class="mt-3">
                  <summary class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm">View Metadata</summary>
                  <pre class="mt-2" style="max-height: 200px; overflow-y: auto; background: #f5f5f5; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;"><%= JSON.pretty_generate(@result[:metadata]) %></pre>
                </details>
              <% end %>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-12">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h5 class="mb-0">Pricing Rules (PRIORITY Hit Policy)</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p>The pricing decision table uses PRIORITY hit policy, meaning rules are evaluated top-to-bottom and the first matching rule wins:</p>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>VIP + Electronics:</strong> 25% discount (highest priority)</li>
            <li><strong>Bulk Electronics (10+):</strong> 20% discount</li>
            <li><strong>Promotional Code (SUMMER2024):</strong> 15% discount</li>
            <li><strong>Books Category:</strong> 10% discount</li>
            <li><strong>Premium Segment:</strong> 10% discount</li>
            <li><strong>Default:</strong> 0% discount (catch-all)</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3">
            <strong>Note:</strong> If multiple rules match, the first one (highest priority) is selected. For example, a VIP customer buying electronics will get 25% discount, not 20% from bulk pricing.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row mt-3">
    <div class="col-12">
      <a href="/demo/all_use_cases" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">‚Üê Back to All Use Cases</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

